Code modified from https://github.com/saideeptiku/Gem5McPatParser

1. Follow the McPAT README to build McPAT
2. Set the `gem5_out_dir` variable in `run_mcpat.sh`, or override it with the `GEM5_OUT_DIR` environment variable, so it points to the Gem5 output directory
3. Run the bash script run_mcpat.sh located in the mcpat folder.
   format: bash run_mcpat.sh print_level if_optimize_clk output_filename
   e.g. bash run_mcpat.sh 2 0 McPAT_out
4. The script auto-creates `McPAT_input/` and `results/` if they do not exist
McPAT output will be stored in the `mcpat/results` folder
